  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Linking Recovery to Resilience is designed to support early recovery for food crisis-affected populations of Ill&#xE9;la and Tahoua departments in Tahoua, Niger through an integrated set of interventions that address key current gaps in livestock and agricultural production. The goal is that the most vulnerable populations in Tahoua, Niger recover from food crisis.

USAID&#x2019;s Office of U.S. Foreign Disaster Assistance (OFDA), LWR and Union Hadin Kai partnered to respond to food insecurity in Tahoua, Niger, by revitalizing local assets and boosting agricultural production for a more resilient future. Key project approaches included:
&#x2022; Cash-for-Work
&#x2022; Soil &amp;amp; Water Conservation
&#x2022; Emergency Seed Provision
&#x2022; Hygiene &amp;amp; Nutritional Health Behavior Change</narrative>
  </description>
